      "writtenOn": "2026-06-01T21:00:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Pushing back on consistency + extensibility grounds, happy to fold if you\u0027d still prefer:\n\nConsistency with peer handlers. chassishandler.hpp (40 LoC, 6 constants), dcmihandler.hpp (51 LoC, 23 constants), and transporthandler.hpp (450 LoC, 8 constants) all keep companion headers carrying command/parameter constants that no other .cpp in this repo includes. pefhandler.hpp follows the same split.\n\nDocumented D-Bus contract surface. The header also documents the PefManager / PefFilter interface contract (object paths, property names, byte layout of the 20-byte filter entry per IPMI 2.0 Table 17.7, pefMaxFilters slot count, ObjectManager requirements). The in-tree provider and the matcher  intentionally carry parallel local copies because they live in separate Yocto recipes that can\u0027t share a header, but they were authored against this contract.\n\nFuture use. Any in-tree provider, mock, or unit test added later naturally #includes the header rather than redefining the constants — that\u0027s the cheap insurance the header buys.",
      "parentUuid": "f61842fc_426c34d2",
      "revId": "43fda67508d4b750f3aad182bd0d97e6425ab0f4",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
